content:
In CRM Analytics, the data type of a dataset column determines how you can query that column's data. For example, you can filter and group by a text or date column, or perform calculations on a number column.

When you load data into a dataset, CRM Analytics sometimes tags a dataset field with the wrong type. Use Data Prep to convert columns to the correct types.

Data type conversion transformations include:

* Text to Date Transformation: Convert the Column Type
* Text to Number Transformation: Convert the Column Type
* Number to Text Transformation: Convert the Column Type

Each transformation changes the column type as follows:
 
* Text to Date: Change a text (dimension) column to a date (measure) column.
* Text to Number: Change a text (dimension) column to a number (measure) column.
* Number to Text: Change a number (measure) column to a text (dimension) column.

Use these transformations in Data Prep recipes to correct data types and perform calculations on your data.
title: Data Type Conversion in CRM Analytics
